cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper deals with 3D object reconstruction using Convolutional Neural Networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on predicting high resolution voxel grids and extracting triangle meshes, which are topics related to computer graphics (cs.GR). The proposed framework also involves hierarchical prediction, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses shape completion from partial voxel grids, which is a topic related to robotics (cs.RO).
